60. What are the important topologies for networks?\par
BUS topology: In this each computer is directly connected to primary network cable in a single line.\par
Advantages: Inexpensive, easy to install, simple to understand, easy to extend.\par
\par
 \par
\par
\par
STAR topology: In this all computers are connected using a central hub.\par
Advantages: Can be inexpensive, easy to install and reconfigure and easy to trouble shoot physical problems.\par
\par
RING topology: In this all computers are connected in loop.\par
Advantages: All computers have equal access to network media, installation can be simple, and signal does not degrade as much as in other topologies because each computer regenerates it.\par
